column5: Guy just backed out last minute, anyone looking to get out for a day of Kawarthas muskie fishing tomorrow send me a PM for details!  Pete
I'd love to ..but can't .   Nice offer.
Sweet offer Pete. Hopefully you find someone.
wish i could man, im going out with a buddy saturday. Good luck
Hopefully someone does, Friday weather looks amazing!
I sold all my musky stuff or i'd be in.
Let me know how it goes, i'm going out saturday
Hope you do better than me.  I was out yesterday - not even a sniff.
Hope you do better than me.  I was out yesterday - not even a sniff.  That's probably Dougs fault though

Boat winterized and tucked away. Wifey and I canoed the shoreline at the cottage on Pigeon today. Trolled a small gold HuskyJerk. Looking for smallies. 2 Muskies in ten minutes.  Unexpected. Both about 36 in. Landed both by hand. No leader. 10 lb nanofil. Was surprised I didn't get bit off. Line in mouth both fish. Last kick at the can. Great way to end

Couldn't have asked for a nicer day on the water - no wind and warm in late Nov... 3 follows and 3 landed. 37" 39" 41", all nice chunky fish. Here's the 39 and 41 pics... I don't think either of these fish have ever soon a lure before, absolutely pristine specimens. It's been a good fall, will be posting a muskie season recap soon.  Cheers Pete
Nice fish boys!
Nice work pete!
Was that first Muskie pictured caught on a top water lure?
Was that first Muskie pictured caught on a top water lure?  Looks like a hellhound, glide bait.  Nice pics Pete!
the 2nd pic the fish is SO CLEAN it's amazing.
Maybe should have joined ya for a day.  Tougher skiing up on the big rivers this past week.
10" hellhound, 10.5 oz glide bait. Lots of fun to cast ? Both fish Josh caught were on it. Mine ate a bulldawg.
Holy crap ive never seen cleaner looking musky! Almost looks fake  Nice going!!!
Nice ones!
Very healthy kawartha skis for sure!
A couple of great looking fish.  Good shooting Pete!
